Observed individual operating a food preparation area without the food service manager having in his ... more Image 32 of 32 Houston restaurant health inspection violations (Oct. 12-18) 1 / 32 Back to Gallery Houston is full of foodies, but that doesn't necessarily mean just getting some grub from a sit-down restaurant.
This week's list of health inspection violators had an interesting mix of venues, including quick-grab eateries like food trucks, fast food joints and gas stations.
The taqueria at Sunshine Food Mart (12800 Northborough Dr.) was temporarily closed down because it couldn't provide hot water -- a major infraction since it means there is no way to properly clean and sanitize the dishes.
While quick-stop places made the list, we did see a couple of tried-and-true favorites from around town, like Ninfa's on Navigation and Aka Sushi House, who had violations as well.
Click the slideshow above to see some of the notable inspections between Oct. 12-18, 2015.
During health inspections, inspectors distribute violations that carry a weight between 1 and 25, increasing in severity. The Houston Chronicle obtained the results of routine health inspections throughout the city and tallied each restaurant's demerits for a comprehensive list of violations.
